":448601,"uid":21028,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-10-27T01:29:30.000Z","msg":"死後可以用 <br />\n因為死後人不能分泌油脂 令死人唔能夠係物件上留下指模 但任何按壓式或滑動式指紋解鎖都一樣唔係因為生物油脂留下既印做解鎖 死人理應可用<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e33538ede5e74e5cae2ee7e4f06b262f7ffc85b0","tid":448601,"uid":44333,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-10-27T01:38:17.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>死後可以用 <br />\n因為死後人不能分泌油脂 令死人唔能夠係物件上留下指模 但任何按壓式或滑動式指紋解鎖都一樣唔係因為生物油脂留下既印做解鎖 死人理應可用<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\nIf you were to touch a dead person's finger to their phone's Touch ID sensor, it wouldn't do anything unless they have just recently died. If you were to send an electrical current through the body, it may activate the capacitive ring but even then wouldn't pass the fingerprint authentication; the way to bypass this is, in theory, to pump warm saline through the blood vessels and touch it to the Touch ID sensor.<br />\n<br />\n一跳完 佢衝落樓黎unlock就應該unlock到"}]}